Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and bilirubinuria, with low-normal glucose and low HbA1c, suggesting significant renal dysfunction (possibly acute or chronic kidney disease) with impaired filtration and possible tubular damage. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) further support renal pathology. Mild metabolic acidosis (low CO₂), hyperchloremia, and low urine specific gravity are also present. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
